5:
You sure this is a good idea? We're
surrounded by ocean in a place that
looks like it's about to fall apart any
second.
7:
One good knock against the walls,
and we'll be breathing sea water.
11:
I know it looks pretty rough in here,
but the outside's super sturdy.
14:
Besides, the good salvage is always
in dangerous spots.
18:
The people of this world never cease
to amaze me—to think they can
make a living by searching through
underwater cities...
22:
Still, we shouldn't stay any longer
than we have to.
26:
Won't argue with you there. Let's get
this job done quick and get—
44:
Oh no, there's no telling how deep
this stretches...
46: Don't worry, I can get him out!
50:
Damn, there's no way I can climb
out on my own.
57:
There you are! Glad to see you're still
in one piece.
66:
Name's Flana! You know, the lightest
salvager in the world?
87: Hehehe, all's well that ends well!
91:
Thanks for the save. Seriously, I owe
you one.
94:
Gotta say though... I'm real confused
how that power of yours works. All
you did was tap me on the shoulder,
and I started floatin' too.
98:
I dunno how it works either! But I'm
pretty sure it's some kinda curse, not
a power!
103:
No point thinking too hard about it
though! More importantly...
106:
Is anyone else here starving, or is it
just me?
113: Thanks for paying for the meal!
117:
It's the least we could do. Please, eat
as much as you like.
121:
You sure eat a lot for someone so
tiny...
124:
Yeah, I have trouble putting on
weight! Never had to worry about
going on a diet my whole life.
129:
So you're telling me... you can eat all
this and not worry about calories?
133: That definitely ain't normal. No way.
136:
Did I hear you right? You mentioned
a curse?
141:
Some years back, I was exploring a
few ruins when I touched this weird
relic.
145: I've been like this ever since then!
150:
Shouldn't you be more... I dunno...
Upset about the whole thing?
153:
Why would I be? I'm not dead, and
I'm perfectly healthy—probably,
anyway!
158:
I guess you could say... nothing
weighs you down, huh...
163:
Oh, that was a clever one! C'mere,
you!
167:
Jokes aside, I have been searching
for a way to get my body back to
normal.
169:
That's why I was exploring those
ruins today. Not that I found
anything though.
173:
Ugh, coming back empty-handed is
just the worst!
177:
If you guys happen to find a method
to fix me, be sure to let me know,
okay?
181:
We'll definitely do our part to search,
but no promises.
185:
Hmm, maybe we can find
something in another world?
193:
Not sure how you'd go about that,
but it sounds like something I should
tag along for!
196:
Hope you don't mind if I join the
team!
